						               													<description>Crueler Seas is a set of optional rules for Warlords naval game Cruel Seas. &amp;#10;They are not designed to be complicated or make the game incredibly realistic. &amp;#10;It keeps the flavor of the original while addressing 2 things that I felt needed to be addressed; namely spotting and the damage model.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It adds rules for:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     spotting,&amp;#10;     differentiating quality of forces during the initiative draw,&amp;#10;     easily re-works the combat system to create a game less of attrition and more of critical hits.  &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It adds 2 expanded critical hit tables, one for small/medium boats and one for larger ships.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Crueler Seas adds a repair chart based on crew quality and finally it has alternate torpedo rules that are similar to the current gun &amp;quot;to hit&amp;quot; procedure rather than the &amp;quot;guess where I am going to be&amp;quot; method.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules are a toolkit so the player can use those he/she feels will enhance their game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ownership of Warlords Cruel Seas is required.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
